<div class="Content">

<div id="LeftColumn">
    <div class="Tab"><a><span>About</span></a></div>
    <div class="BlueBox">
    <p>
            BOMP is a tool for prediction of beta-barrel integral outer membrane 
            proteins (BOMPs). The user may submit a list of proteins, and receive a 
            list of predicted BOMPs.
        </p>
        
        <ul>
            <li><a href="Information/instructions">Instructions </a> </li>
            <li><a href="Information/outputinfo">Output</a> </li>
            <li>
                <a href="Information/wholeproteomes">
                    Integral &szlig;-barrel outer membrane proteins predicted from 
                    whole proteomes
                </a>
            </li>
            <li>
                <a href="Information/blastdb">
                    Database used in BLAST homolgy search
                </a>
            </li>
            <li>
                <a href="Information/finalrefset">
                    Final reference set in the amino acid distribution filter
                </a>
            </li>
            <li>
                <a href="Information/refset">
                    Reference set (after homolgy reducing)
                </a>
            </li>
        </ul>
        
    </div>
    
    <div class="WhiteBar"></div>
    
    <div class="Tab"><a><span>Problems</span></a></div>
    <div class="BlueBox">
        <p>
            Send an email to
            <a href="mailto:services@cbu.uib.no">services@cbu.uib.no</a>
        </p>
    </div>

</div>


<div id="RightColumn">
<h1>BOMP - The &szlig;-barrel outer membrane protein predictor</h1>

<form action="handleForm" method="post" enctype="multipart/form-data">

    <fieldset>
        <label>
            Enter one or more protein sequence(s) in 
            <a href="Information/fasta">FASTA</a> format:
        </label>
        <textarea name="seqs" rows="20" cols="65"></textarea>
        
        <label>
            <input type="checkbox" name="useblast" id="blast">
            Use BLAST to get additional information (will increase running time)
        </label>
        <label>E-Value:</label>
        <select name="evalue">
            <option value=0.0000000001>1e-10</option>
            <option value=0.1>0.1</option>
            <option value=0.00001>1e-5</option>
            <option value=0.000001>1e-6</option>
            <option value=0.0000001>1e-7</option>
            <option value=0.00000001>1e-8</option>
            <option value=0.000000001>1e-9</option>
            <option value=0.0000000001>1e-10</option>
            <option value=0.00000000001>1e-11</option>
            <option value=0.000000000001>1e-12</option>
            <option value=0.0000000000001>1e-13</option>
            <option value=0.00000000000001>1e-14</option>
            <option value=0.000000000000001>1e-15</option>
        </select>
        
        <label>
            Submission of a local file in <a href="Information/fasta">fasta</a>
            format
        </label>
        <input type="FILE" name="queryfile" size="40"> 
        
        <label>
            <input type="SUBMIT" name="SUBMIT" value="Submit Search">
            <input type="reset" value="Reset Form">
        </label>
    </fieldset>
</form>

<h2>Citation</h2>

<p>
    If you use BOMP in your research, we would greatly appreciate if you cited
    the following publication:
</p>
    
<p>
    Berven FS, Flikka K, Jensen HB, Eidhammer I. 
    <a href="http://www.pubmedcentral.nih.gov/articlerender.fcgi?tool=pubmed&pubmedid=15215418">
        BOMP: a program to predict integral beta-barrel outer membrane proteins 
        encoded within genomes of Gram-negative bacteria
    </a>. Nucleic Acids Res. 2004 Jul 1;32(Web Server issue):W394-9
</p>

